ts<\/a>, or even short emails, the following ideas for short and sweet greetings are sure to please.<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Happy Labor Day to the workers of every field! The world runs on your contributions and you all deserve respect, recognition, and a day to relax. We hope you have a great one!<\/li>\n<li>Today is a tribute to those who work. Paid or unpaid, part-time or full, happily or not (but hopefully happily)\u2014you help make the world go round. Thank you and Happy Labor Day!<\/li>\n<li>Happy Labor Day everyone! Thank you for your tireless work. Now kick back, relax, and enjoy your day off. You\u2019ve earned it!<\/li>\n<li>To all hardworking employees: Happy Labor Day! And a special shout out to those who work hard to protect workers\u2019 rights. Thank you all for making our world a better place to live and work in.<\/li>\n<li>Happy Labor Day weekend to our employees, customers, and partners. Take a load off and enjoy one last summer hurrah!<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/labor-day-messages-email-headers-4.png\" alt=\"labor day messages - happy labor day email banner with american flag border\" width=\"600\" height=\"200\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-63629\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/labor-day-messages-email-headers-4.png 600w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/08\/labor-day-messages-email-headers-4-480x160.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 600px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><a href=\"https:\/\/marketing.wordstream.com\/WSLIQContentDLWebsite120WordsforMarketingWithEmotion.html?cid=Web_Any_BlogInContent_PPC_120WordsPhrases_Download&amp;utm_souce=web&amp;utm_medium=blog&amp;utm_campaign=laborday\"><\/a><\/p>\n<h2>Labor Day email banners<\/h2>\n<p>All of the images in this post are standard email header size (600 x 200px), so you can save them right off of the post 